1
00:00:14,367 --> 00:00:15,667
<i> Hey! What's this?</i>

2
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:17,200
<i> Who are you? I don't know you!</i>

3
00:00:17,333 --> 00:00:18,233
<i> Dad! Uncle!</i>

4
00:00:18,367 --> 00:00:20,133
<i> These are the flight details.</i>

5
00:00:20,267 --> 00:00:23,033
<i>Yes, sir. The plane landed
about an hour ago.</i>

6
00:00:29,867 --> 00:00:30,833
<i> Jeff texted.</i>

7
00:00:31,867 --> 00:00:32,700
<i> What did he say?</i>

8
00:00:32,833 --> 00:00:35,400
<i>"Sorry, I couldn't make it home.</i>

9
00:00:35,567 --> 00:00:37,400
<i> There was an emergency."</i>

10
00:00:41,067 --> 00:00:43,633
<i>This isn't how I imagined
revenge, Hazel.</i>

11
00:00:43,767 --> 00:00:47,300
<i>I thought we were just
going to ruin Manuel's family.</i>

12
00:00:47,433 --> 00:00:48,400
<i> Why?</i>

13
00:00:49,567 --> 00:00:50,433
<i> Getting cold feet?</i>

14
00:00:50,567 --> 00:00:52,000
<i> Daisy!</i>

15
00:00:52,133 --> 00:00:53,633
<i> Where's Dad?</i>

16
00:00:53,767 --> 00:00:54,933
<i> He's not here yet.</i>

17
00:00:55,067 --> 00:00:57,667
<i>He texted earlier.
Said he couldn't make it.</i>

18
00:00:57,800 --> 00:00:59,067
<i> No, he did make it, Auntie.</i>

19
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:01,433
<i>I know who did this.
It was Hazel.</i>

20
00:01:01,567 --> 00:01:03,867
<i>That demon
hasn't changed at all!</i>

21
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:05,233
<i>- Andrea!
- Andrea!</i>

22
00:01:05,367 --> 00:01:07,867
<i>- Sis!
- Don't hurt Andrea!</i>

23
00:01:08,033 --> 00:01:09,667
<i>Where's my brother?
Bring him out!</i>

24
00:01:09,800 --> 00:01:11,467
<i>Get out of here,
all of you!</i>

25
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:12,533
<i> Get out!</i>

26
00:01:12,667 --> 00:01:14,433
<i>We received a report
of trespassing.</i>

27
00:01:14,567 --> 00:01:16,067
<i>Arrest them,
especially that woman!</i>

28
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:17,667
<i> Look! Look at her!</i>

29
00:01:21,067 --> 00:01:24,033
Mrs. Hazel Cruz, you're the one
filing the complaint?

30
00:01:24,167 --> 00:01:25,500
Yes.

31
00:01:25,633 --> 00:01:29,967
They barged into my house.

32
00:01:30,100 --> 00:01:31,300
She attacked me.

33
00:01:31,433 --> 00:01:36,433
Because you murdered my friend
and had my brother kidnapped!

34
00:01:37,667 --> 00:01:38,867
Andrea.

35
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:41,100
Enough, sweetheart. Please.

36
00:01:42,733 --> 00:01:43,733
Andrea...

37
00:01:43,867 --> 00:01:46,100
don't waste your time on her.

38
00:01:46,233 --> 00:01:48,533
I can't just stay
quiet, Uncle.

39
00:01:48,667 --> 00:01:50,800
Miss Chairwoman, this woman

40
00:01:50,933 --> 00:01:53,133
has done terrible things
to my family.

41
00:01:53,267 --> 00:01:55,867
She did so many
evil things to us!

42
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:59,100
I'm sorry,
but that's not my concern.

43
00:01:59,233 --> 00:02:03,767
Mrs. Cruz's complaint
is trespassing.

44
00:02:03,900 --> 00:02:05,033
And assault.

45
00:02:05,167 --> 00:02:07,833
Hazel, can we just let this go?

46
00:02:07,967 --> 00:02:10,400
Can you not get involved, Noah?

47
00:02:10,533 --> 00:02:13,333
You're always there. Why?
Who are you, anyway?

48
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:16,000
Let's keep our voices down.

49
00:02:16,133 --> 00:02:19,333
Mrs. Cruz, would you like
to discuss this or...

50
00:02:19,467 --> 00:02:21,233
I'm pressing charges.

51
00:02:21,367 --> 00:02:24,000
I'll file a restraining
order against them.

52
00:02:24,133 --> 00:02:25,467
Hazel, can you not?

53
00:02:26,600 --> 00:02:28,033
Why shouldn't I?

54
00:02:28,167 --> 00:02:29,433
Mind your own business!

55
00:02:29,567 --> 00:02:32,333
When you violated a restraining
order before,

56
00:02:32,467 --> 00:02:35,000
I had it dismissed
by Atty. Yeban.

57
00:02:35,133 --> 00:02:36,533
So what?

58
00:02:36,667 --> 00:02:38,167
Are we keeping score now?

59
00:02:38,300 --> 00:02:39,500
Yes.

60
00:02:39,633 --> 00:02:41,533
Because if I hadn't done that,

61
00:02:41,667 --> 00:02:43,833
you'd be in jail right now.

62
00:02:57,300 --> 00:02:59,567
It's a good thing Coleen
convinced Hazel...

63
00:02:59,700 --> 00:03:02,633
not to file charges.

64
00:03:02,767 --> 00:03:05,867
Here, I made some coffee
to calm everyone down.

65
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:12,233
This won't calm your nerves.
Maybe juice instead.

66
00:03:12,367 --> 00:03:15,967
Coffee's fine, Didang.

67
00:03:16,100 --> 00:03:17,867
- Oh, sir.
- Yeah.

68
00:03:20,233 --> 00:03:22,467
Where could they
have taken Jeffrey?

69
00:03:24,067 --> 00:03:26,000
Don't worry, Andeng.

70
00:03:26,133 --> 00:03:28,300
We won't stop
looking for him.

71
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:41,267
Hello, Colonel Sarabia?

72
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:46,900
It's my fault.

73
00:03:47,033 --> 00:03:49,367
I shouldn't have
let Jeff come home.

74
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:50,800
I should've stopped him.

75
00:03:50,933 --> 00:03:53,400
- This is my fault...
- Andeng, stop.

76
00:03:53,533 --> 00:03:55,633
Don't blame yourself.

77
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:59,100
Yeah.

78
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:02,633
It's Hazel.

79
00:04:02,767 --> 00:04:04,900
She's behind all of this.

80
00:04:06,233 --> 00:04:08,167
She's a monster.

81
00:04:08,300 --> 00:04:12,433
If she hurts my brother,
I swear.

82
00:04:12,567 --> 00:04:14,467
Hazel's evilness...

83
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:17,000
won't win.

84
00:04:17,133 --> 00:04:19,333
We'll find your brother.

85
00:04:21,067 --> 00:04:22,367
No one's giving up.

86
00:04:24,133 --> 00:04:25,467
Not now.

87
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:27,367
Not ever.

88
00:04:29,633 --> 00:04:30,700
But wait.

89
00:04:32,767 --> 00:04:35,367
If Hazel kidnapped Jeff,

90
00:04:37,533 --> 00:04:40,900
how did she know
his flight details?

91
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:06,233
<i>When they found out Jessica
wasn't really their sister,</i>

92
00:05:06,367 --> 00:05:07,667
<i> they hurt her.</i>

93
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:11,367
<i>They abused her
until she got depressed.</i>

94
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:13,367
<i> Until our daughter died.</i>

95
00:05:14,467 --> 00:05:16,967
<i>Even if Jessica wasn't
their real sister,</i>

96
00:05:17,100 --> 00:05:19,300
<i> they treated her like one.</i>

97
00:05:19,433 --> 00:05:22,200
<i>They never saw her
as just a half-sister.</i>

98
00:05:22,333 --> 00:05:28,000
<i>Felma accepted her
as her own child.</i>

99
00:05:28,133 --> 00:05:33,633
<i>Joel and Jessica came
into our lives.</i>

100
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:36,567
<i> Especially Jessica.</i>

101
00:05:36,700 --> 00:05:40,967
<i> I loved that child so much.</i>

102
00:05:41,100 --> 00:05:43,267
<i>And you're blaming us
for her death?</i>

103
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:45,200
<i> That happened because of you.</i>

104
00:05:45,333 --> 00:05:47,100
<i> Because of what you did!</i>

105
00:05:48,267 --> 00:05:50,767
<i>Hazel, killing someone
was never part of the plan.</i>

106
00:05:50,900 --> 00:05:51,800
<i> Just me?</i>

107
00:05:52,900 --> 00:05:54,200
<i> No. We.</i>

108
00:05:54,333 --> 00:05:56,067
<i> You're part of this, too.</i>

109
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:04,167
Jojo?

110
00:06:05,133 --> 00:06:06,233
Jojo.

111
00:06:07,667 --> 00:06:08,933
Jojo.

112
00:06:09,067 --> 00:06:10,300
Are you okay?

113
00:06:10,433 --> 00:06:11,367
Why did you text me?

114
00:06:12,767 --> 00:06:14,067
I'm so confused.

115
00:06:17,100 --> 00:06:19,767
What Hazel says about
Manuel's family doesn't add up.

116
00:06:21,533 --> 00:06:23,333
What do you mean?

117
00:06:23,467 --> 00:06:26,100
I have a really bad image
of Manuel's family.

118
00:06:27,300 --> 00:06:28,933
A few times,

119
00:06:29,067 --> 00:06:30,767
sure...

120
00:06:30,900 --> 00:06:32,900
maybe...

121
00:06:33,033 --> 00:06:36,300
people can fake kindness.

122
00:06:36,433 --> 00:06:37,733
But theirs is consistent.

123
00:06:39,700 --> 00:06:43,567
I want to keep
hating his family.

124
00:06:45,067 --> 00:06:46,667
But...

125
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,000
Alice,

126
00:06:48,133 --> 00:06:49,433
tell me.

127
00:06:49,567 --> 00:06:50,800
What do you know?

128
00:06:51,833 --> 00:06:53,633
Is what Hazel's saying true?

129
00:06:56,167 --> 00:06:57,867
Do you really want to know?

130
00:06:59,233 --> 00:07:00,300
Yes.

131
00:07:06,333 --> 00:07:08,167
<i> Try turning on me.</i>

132
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:10,567
<i>You know me well enough, right?</i>

133
00:07:10,700 --> 00:07:12,900
<i> You know what I'm capable of.</i>

134
00:07:13,033 --> 00:07:14,833
<i> No matter who it is.</i>

135
00:07:15,967 --> 00:07:17,300
<i> Hi, Alice.</i>

136
00:07:17,433 --> 00:07:19,633
<i>What are you and Jojo
talking about?</i>

137
00:07:19,767 --> 00:07:21,567
<i> Care to share?</i>

138
00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:24,300
<i> Why'd you suddenly go quiet?</i>

139
00:07:39,633 --> 00:07:41,400
Hazel's a good friend.

140
00:07:42,433 --> 00:07:44,267
That's not what I asked.

141
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:45,733
What do you know?

142
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:48,567
Alice...

143
00:07:48,733 --> 00:07:50,467
you're hiding something.

144
00:07:53,300 --> 00:07:57,633
Come on. Why are you asking me
all this?

145
00:07:57,767 --> 00:07:59,567
Talk to Hazel yourself.

146
00:07:59,700 --> 00:08:01,267
I might say...

147
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:03,233
something I shouldn't.

148
00:08:48,367 --> 00:08:49,733
How are you, Jeff?

149
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:54,133
Still holding up?

150
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:57,100
Hazel.

151
00:08:57,233 --> 00:08:58,967
I knew this was you.

152
00:09:02,067 --> 00:09:03,433
I'm touched.

153
00:09:04,867 --> 00:09:06,733
You really do
know me well.

154
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:13,400
You knew I'd be
your special guest.

155
00:09:16,400 --> 00:09:17,700
Let me go.

156
00:09:17,833 --> 00:09:20,400
Let me out of here!
Why did you bring me here?

157
00:09:20,533 --> 00:09:21,900
Let me go!

158
00:09:22,033 --> 00:09:23,233
You monster!

159
00:09:23,367 --> 00:09:25,067
Monster!

160
00:09:28,733 --> 00:09:30,100
You're evil!

161
00:09:37,500 --> 00:09:38,833
According to Colonel Sarabia,

162
00:09:38,967 --> 00:09:44,367
the hair follicle test showed
Joel wasn't a regular drug user.

163
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:48,200
So they're focusing on possible
foul play.

164
00:09:48,333 --> 00:09:51,433
That's what I've been saying
from the start.

165
00:09:52,733 --> 00:09:54,533
Joel wasn't an addict.

166
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,867
Of course, dear.

167
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:58,300
We believe you.

168
00:09:59,133 --> 00:10:01,333
What about Jeff's case?
Any updates?

169
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:04,033
Have they checked
the airport CCTVs?

170
00:10:05,167 --> 00:10:06,833
Here.

171
00:10:06,967 --> 00:10:09,967
Based on the footage
Colonel Sarabia brought,

172
00:10:10,100 --> 00:10:11,533
you can see Jeffrey here.

173
00:10:11,667 --> 00:10:14,533
Then a white van pulls up.

174
00:10:14,667 --> 00:10:16,133
It stops for a moment.

175
00:10:16,267 --> 00:10:18,267
When it moves again,

176
00:10:18,400 --> 00:10:20,233
Jeffrey's gone.

177
00:10:20,367 --> 00:10:23,067
Sir Manuel,
that's you and Sir Abel.

178
00:10:23,867 --> 00:10:25,933
- Oh, yeah.
- That's right, Dad.

179
00:10:26,067 --> 00:10:27,433
And the interval...

180
00:10:28,567 --> 00:10:32,533
You almost ran into Jeffrey
if the van hadn't blocked you.

181
00:10:32,667 --> 00:10:33,833
Too bad.

182
00:10:37,700 --> 00:10:40,900
Even though they didn't
see Jeffrey get in,

183
00:10:41,033 --> 00:10:43,167
they're investigating
the white van.

184
00:10:43,300 --> 00:10:45,600
I also hired
a private investigator.

185
00:10:45,733 --> 00:10:47,133
Just to be sure.

186
00:10:47,267 --> 00:10:49,533
Van kidnappings
are common these days.

187
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:54,367
What's strange is that
it's been days already.

188
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:56,767
No ransom demand.

189
00:10:56,900 --> 00:10:59,633
Unless they have another
motive for Jeff.

190
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:07,567
Why are you doing this
to my family?

191
00:11:09,767 --> 00:11:10,700
Do you even have to ask?

192
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:13,567
It's simple.

193
00:11:14,700 --> 00:11:16,567
I want revenge.

194
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:20,233
I want to collect
on everything you owe me.

195
00:11:20,367 --> 00:11:23,600
You're the one
who owes us, Hazel.

196
00:11:23,733 --> 00:11:25,133
Ever since you took our father.

197
00:11:25,267 --> 00:11:27,033
Ever since you got
pregnant in Saudi Arabia.

198
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:30,500
Fine.

199
00:11:30,633 --> 00:11:32,033
Let's count, then.

200
00:11:32,167 --> 00:11:33,500
I'll make the
list for you.

201
00:11:35,267 --> 00:11:38,033
First...

202
00:11:38,167 --> 00:11:41,067
I filed charges against Coleen
for what happened to Jessica.

203
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,867
And...

204
00:11:43,033 --> 00:11:47,200
recently,
when she almost got hurt?

205
00:11:47,333 --> 00:11:49,133
That was me, too.

206
00:11:50,567 --> 00:11:53,100
You animal!

207
00:11:53,233 --> 00:11:54,600
Let me out of here!

208
00:11:55,900 --> 00:11:56,867
There's more.

209
00:11:57,000 --> 00:12:00,433
What I asked them to do
to Andrea was simple.

210
00:12:00,567 --> 00:12:02,900
I told my guy to harass her.

211
00:12:03,033 --> 00:12:04,600
- And he did.
- You shameless monster!

212
00:12:04,733 --> 00:12:07,033
Come here! Monster!

213
00:12:07,167 --> 00:12:09,033
You're disgusting!

214
00:12:09,167 --> 00:12:10,900
You don't deserve any respect!

215
00:12:13,633 --> 00:12:15,000
And then there's Joel...

216
00:12:16,467 --> 00:12:17,833
Honestly,

217
00:12:18,967 --> 00:12:21,000
that jerk
wasn't even on my list.

218
00:12:22,033 --> 00:12:23,700
Who was he, right?

219
00:12:23,833 --> 00:12:25,533
He meant nothing to me.

220
00:12:25,667 --> 00:12:29,067
But he tried to be a hero.

221
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:31,300
Showing off for all of you.

222
00:12:31,433 --> 00:12:33,300
So he got dragged into it.

223
00:12:33,433 --> 00:12:36,133
Hazel, so you have something
to do with Joel's death.

224
00:12:36,267 --> 00:12:37,667
You're a demon!

225
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:40,033
Pure evil!
You're a monster, Hazel!

226
00:12:41,133 --> 00:12:42,133
Hold on.

227
00:12:43,567 --> 00:12:46,967
You know, if you really think
about it,

228
00:12:47,100 --> 00:12:50,333
you people are the reason
Joel died.

229
00:12:50,500 --> 00:12:54,133
Andrea, to be exact.

230
00:12:54,267 --> 00:12:56,167
She let that man into her life.

231
00:12:56,300 --> 00:12:58,533
So I was forced
to dispose of him.

232
00:12:58,667 --> 00:12:59,867
You're a murderer!

233
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:02,100
You're a monster!

234
00:13:02,233 --> 00:13:03,367
Murderer!

235
00:13:03,500 --> 00:13:06,033
That man had nothing to do
with this, and you killed him!

236
00:13:06,167 --> 00:13:08,333
Didn't you hear what I said?

237
00:13:08,467 --> 00:13:12,000
I didn't mean to.
I didn't want to do it.

238
00:13:12,133 --> 00:13:15,300
But I had no choice.
Better him than me, right?

239
00:13:17,700 --> 00:13:18,967
You know what?

240
00:13:20,067 --> 00:13:21,533
You guys...

241
00:13:21,700 --> 00:13:24,233
bring out the worst in me.

242
00:13:24,367 --> 00:13:27,533
So if you think about it,
this is your fault.

243
00:13:27,667 --> 00:13:30,300
Joel's death is on you.
Do you understand?

244
00:13:31,667 --> 00:13:33,367
You're evil, Hazel.

245
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:35,667
You're worse than a demon.

246
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:38,667
Even demons should be scared
of you. If I get out of here...

247
00:13:38,800 --> 00:13:40,400
If I escape,
I'll get my revenge.

248
00:13:40,533 --> 00:13:44,200
I don't care if you're a woman!
I'll kill you!

249
00:13:44,333 --> 00:13:46,100
- I'll get my revenge!
- Oh, relax.

250
00:13:46,233 --> 00:13:49,733
Let me out of here!
Let me go! Let me go!

251
00:13:49,867 --> 00:13:51,967
I'm so scared! Jeff, no!

252
00:13:52,100 --> 00:13:53,267
Don't!

253
00:13:55,867 --> 00:13:57,700
Go on. Gag him already.
He talks too much.

254
00:13:57,833 --> 00:13:59,200
Let me go!

255
00:13:59,333 --> 00:14:01,000
Let me go!

256
00:14:01,133 --> 00:14:02,467
Do whatever you want.

257
00:14:17,233 --> 00:14:18,700
Go, just cry.

258
00:14:41,433 --> 00:14:42,667
Why do you look so scared?

259
00:14:43,267 --> 00:14:44,733
Like you just saw a killer.

260
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,233
Aren't you?

261
00:14:51,633 --> 00:14:53,367
What do you even want?

262
00:14:55,267 --> 00:14:56,567
I came to visit you.

263
00:14:57,933 --> 00:15:00,700
It's been a while
since we last talked.

264
00:15:00,833 --> 00:15:04,267
Maybe you missed me, friend.

265
00:15:06,700 --> 00:15:08,467
I've just been busy lately.

266
00:15:09,433 --> 00:15:11,167
And...

267
00:15:11,300 --> 00:15:14,000
I told you, didn't I?

268
00:15:14,133 --> 00:15:15,867
I'm starting to grow
a conscience.

269
00:15:16,967 --> 00:15:19,367
And I'm just following
what you told me. To shut up.

270
00:15:19,500 --> 00:15:21,067
So I really did.

271
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:24,167
Jojo's been bugging me.

272
00:15:24,300 --> 00:15:26,333
But I didn't tell him anything.

273
00:15:26,467 --> 00:15:28,933
You haven't said anything yet.

274
00:15:30,700 --> 00:15:33,267
Because you know I've got eyes
all over this hospital.

275
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:36,733
If I didn't,

276
00:15:36,900 --> 00:15:39,500
you would've sold me out
a long time ago.

277
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:43,567
I really didn't, friend.
Promise.

278
00:15:44,900 --> 00:15:46,667
I won't tell him anything.

279
00:15:47,700 --> 00:15:48,633
Come on.

280
00:15:48,767 --> 00:15:50,067
Let's go home together.

281
00:15:53,433 --> 00:15:54,633
Manuel,

282
00:15:55,700 --> 00:15:57,367
what if...

283
00:15:57,500 --> 00:16:00,700
what if Jeffrey wasn't taken...

284
00:16:00,833 --> 00:16:02,900
for ransom, but...

285
00:16:05,033 --> 00:16:06,567
My god.

286
00:16:06,700 --> 00:16:08,800
I hope not.

287
00:16:09,867 --> 00:16:12,900
I want to tell you not
to think like that.

288
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:18,600
But I can't help it either.

289
00:16:21,100 --> 00:16:23,733
Daisy's ex,

290
00:16:23,867 --> 00:16:25,133
the one we had locked up.

291
00:16:26,467 --> 00:16:29,400
What if he got out?
What if he escaped?

292
00:16:30,400 --> 00:16:32,433
Does he have people outside?

293
00:16:32,567 --> 00:16:33,800
What if he found out

294
00:16:33,933 --> 00:16:37,867
Jeffrey, Daisy, and Tetay
were reunited in Australia?

295
00:16:39,500 --> 00:16:41,900
What if he's getting revenge?

296
00:16:42,067 --> 00:16:43,833
That's possible.

297
00:16:45,133 --> 00:16:47,700
I'll check on it tomorrow.
I'll bring Abel with me.

298
00:16:49,033 --> 00:16:51,967
But something else
keeps bothering me.

299
00:16:52,100 --> 00:16:54,300
What happened to Jeffrey...

300
00:16:54,433 --> 00:16:56,133
Joel's death.

301
00:16:56,267 --> 00:17:00,167
And what just happened
to Coleen and Andrea...

302
00:17:00,300 --> 00:17:02,167
It's like someone's playing
with us.

303
00:17:02,300 --> 00:17:04,033
No, a demon.

304
00:17:06,167 --> 00:17:09,067
I feel like
cracking her skull open

305
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:16,600
just to see what kind
of twisted brain she has.

306
00:17:23,067 --> 00:17:25,200
Why are you asking
Alice questions?

307
00:17:25,333 --> 00:17:27,367
What are you
trying to find out?

308
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:29,033
Do you doubt me?

309
00:17:34,033 --> 00:17:35,400
Hazel,

310
00:17:35,533 --> 00:17:37,200
what you're saying about how
Manuel's family treated Jessica

311
00:17:37,333 --> 00:17:42,033
doesn't match what I've seen.

312
00:17:42,167 --> 00:17:46,500
It's hard
to fake kindness forever.

313
00:17:46,633 --> 00:17:50,000
The truth always shows.

314
00:17:50,167 --> 00:17:52,367
So what are you implying?

315
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:53,833
That I'm lying?

316
00:17:54,733 --> 00:17:56,400
I don't know.

317
00:17:56,533 --> 00:17:58,700
Something feels off.

318
00:17:58,833 --> 00:18:02,600
If you don't believe me
anymore,

319
00:18:02,733 --> 00:18:05,633
if you don't like how I do
things, just say it.

320
00:18:05,767 --> 00:18:07,467
I'll get revenge for
my daughter myself.

321
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:08,967
Stay out of it.

322
00:18:09,100 --> 00:18:12,300
After all, you were never
really there for Jessica anyway.

323
00:18:12,433 --> 00:18:14,500
What could we expect from you?

324
00:18:14,633 --> 00:18:17,633
Hazel, all I'm asking is that...

325
00:18:17,767 --> 00:18:22,367
you're honest about what I need
to know about Jessica.

326
00:18:22,533 --> 00:18:26,933
Maybe our anger
and revenge on Manuel's family,

327
00:18:27,067 --> 00:18:28,767
who isn't as evil as we think,
have gone too far.

328
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:31,500
Just admit it.
You're scared.

329
00:18:31,633 --> 00:18:32,867
You're backing out.

330
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:34,867
Let me remind you.

331
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:37,867
You're already involved
in Joel's death.

332
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:39,867
It's fine if you want out.

333
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:41,700
Just don't turn me in.

334
00:18:41,833 --> 00:18:43,600
Because if you do,

335
00:18:43,733 --> 00:18:45,600
you're going down with me.

336
00:19:06,100 --> 00:19:08,233
Who's that man with Hazel?

337
00:19:11,033 --> 00:19:12,767
Help! Help!

338
00:19:38,533 --> 00:19:39,967
Here you go, Ma'am.

339
00:19:45,367 --> 00:19:48,733
Miss Felma, are you okay?

340
00:19:48,867 --> 00:19:50,233
Is something bothering you?

341
00:19:51,233 --> 00:19:52,533
Sorry.

342
00:19:54,500 --> 00:19:56,633
I just needed to let it out.

343
00:19:57,733 --> 00:20:01,333
It's hard for a mother

344
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:08,433
when you don't know
what's happening to your child.

345
00:20:08,567 --> 00:20:09,733
Why?

346
00:20:09,867 --> 00:20:10,900
Is there still no news

347
00:20:11,033 --> 00:20:12,067
about Jeffrey?

348
00:20:18,100 --> 00:20:22,433
Every day that passes,

349
00:20:22,567 --> 00:20:30,333
the fear gets worse.

350
00:20:32,100 --> 00:20:33,467
What if...

351
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:35,733
something bad happened to him?

352
00:20:37,767 --> 00:20:39,700
Where could he be?

353
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:43,200
Is he eating on time?

354
00:20:45,033 --> 00:20:46,800
Is someone hurting him?

355
00:20:48,067 --> 00:20:53,800
Who took him
if he really was kidnapped?

356
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:03,467
Can I take a quick
bathroom break?

357
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:05,433
Oh, sure, Ma'am.

358
00:21:51,367 --> 00:21:52,167
That's my phone!

359
00:21:52,300 --> 00:21:55,367
- What's that?
- My phone!

360
00:21:56,067 --> 00:21:57,633
That's mine!

361
00:21:57,767 --> 00:22:02,033
That father-and-daughter
moment is so cute, right?

362
00:22:02,167 --> 00:22:04,200
It reminds me of Jessica.

363
00:22:04,333 --> 00:22:06,667
Your kid's cute, too. Look.

364
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:09,100
To be fair,
you really are Manuel's son.

365
00:22:09,233 --> 00:22:12,133
He was just as sweet to Jessica.

366
00:22:12,267 --> 00:22:14,400
You shameless witch!

367
00:22:14,533 --> 00:22:15,567
Give it back! That's mine!

368
00:22:15,733 --> 00:22:17,000
Don't touch it!

369
00:22:17,133 --> 00:22:19,233
You know...

370
00:22:19,367 --> 00:22:22,367
I'm sure your family
misses you so much.

371
00:22:22,500 --> 00:22:24,500
They're probably looking
everywhere for you.

372
00:22:24,633 --> 00:22:25,933
Desperate to find you.

373
00:22:26,067 --> 00:22:27,400
What do you think?

374
00:22:28,733 --> 00:22:32,000
I'm sure they can't wait
to hug you,

375
00:22:32,133 --> 00:22:35,200
be with you, be a family again.

376
00:22:36,233 --> 00:22:37,867
But...

377
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:39,333
how should I say this?

378
00:22:39,467 --> 00:22:41,133
That's never
going to happen.

379
00:22:41,267 --> 00:22:42,667
Ever.

380
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:45,067
But you know what?

381
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:46,300
I just had an idea.

382
00:22:46,433 --> 00:22:53,200
What if we give them
photographs and memories?

383
00:22:53,367 --> 00:22:54,633
Right?

384
00:22:54,767 --> 00:22:56,433
Let's give them that.

385
00:22:56,567 --> 00:22:58,233
So, game?

386
00:22:58,367 --> 00:23:00,433
Brilliant idea. Admit it.

387
00:23:00,567 --> 00:23:03,833
- You're a monster!
- All right. Get ready.

388
00:23:03,967 --> 00:23:05,267
Ready, ready, ready.

389
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:07,133
Okay, hold it.

390
00:23:07,267 --> 00:23:10,600
- Ouch!
- Smile!

391
00:23:10,733 --> 00:23:12,200
Now, go wacky.

392
00:23:12,333 --> 00:23:14,133
Wacky!

393
00:23:16,300 --> 00:23:17,433
Here, over here.

394
00:23:17,567 --> 00:23:18,667
Angle it this way.

395
00:23:18,800 --> 00:23:20,800
It doesn't look nice.
Fix it up.

396
00:23:20,933 --> 00:23:22,633
We're sending
this to them.

397
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:26,067
- One, two, three, smile!
- Monster!

398
00:23:27,967 --> 00:23:29,300
Look, look!

399
00:23:29,433 --> 00:23:30,300
Oh, wow!

400
00:23:30,433 --> 00:23:31,633
I'm good, aren't I?

401
00:23:31,767 --> 00:23:33,100
Great shot!

402
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:39,500
So, who should I send this
to first?

403
00:23:39,633 --> 00:23:41,800
Felma?

404
00:23:41,933 --> 00:23:43,233
Manuel?

405
00:23:43,367 --> 00:23:45,233
Or Andrea, that nasty girl?

406
00:23:45,367 --> 00:23:47,100
Maybe her first?

407
00:23:47,233 --> 00:23:50,433
Or how about your baby sister,
Coleen?

408
00:23:50,567 --> 00:23:52,133
Who? Tell me.

409
00:23:52,267 --> 00:23:53,933
Go die!

410
00:23:54,067 --> 00:23:55,700
I hope you die!

411
00:23:56,867 --> 00:23:58,833
My phone!

412
00:23:58,967 --> 00:24:00,033
That's my phone!

413
00:24:00,167 --> 00:24:01,767
Okay.

414
00:24:01,900 --> 00:24:03,967
You're thanking me?

415
00:24:04,100 --> 00:24:06,233
You're welcome, Jeffrey.

416
00:24:06,367 --> 00:24:08,200
The pleasure is mine.

417
00:24:10,733 --> 00:24:11,833
That shot looks amazing!

418
00:24:20,100 --> 00:24:21,400
Where did she go?

419
00:24:21,533 --> 00:24:23,667
She disappeared so fast.

420
00:24:23,800 --> 00:24:25,300
Looking for me?

421
00:24:26,667 --> 00:24:27,933
Are you stalking me?

422
00:24:28,067 --> 00:24:31,500
Maybe you could ask Madam
Hazel when she comes later.

423
00:24:31,667 --> 00:24:32,833
Let's just ask for ransom.

424
00:24:32,967 --> 00:24:34,467
Yeah, boss.

425
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:37,000
You animal!

426
00:24:37,133 --> 00:24:38,833
You animal!

427
00:24:38,967 --> 00:24:39,933
It's hard, Manuel.

428
00:24:40,067 --> 00:24:43,233
I just want to be sure
Jeffrey's okay.

429
00:24:43,367 --> 00:24:47,300
I'm sure God won't abandon
our firstborn.
